<subSubSection pageNumber="732" type="discussion">
<paragraph pageNumber="732">
<emphasis italics="true" pageNumber="732">Note:</emphasis>
An illegitimate replacement name for 
<taxonomicName authority="L. (1753)" authorityName=", Simpla" authorityYear="1753" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Lamiaceae" genus="Ocimum" kingdom="Plantae" order="Lamiales" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="frutescens">
<emphasis italics="true" pageNumber="732">Ocimum frutescens</emphasis>
L. (1753)
</taxonomicName>
and hence homotypic with it. Hedge (in Ali &amp; Nasir, 
<emphasis italics="true" pageNumber="732">Fl. Pakistan</emphasis>
192: 265. 1990) designated 731.2 (LINN) as the type of 
<taxonomicName authorityName=", Simpla" authorityYear="1753" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Lamiaceae" genus="Ocimum" kingdom="Plantae" order="Lamiales" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="frutescens">
<emphasis italics="true" pageNumber="732">O. frutescens</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
but this is an Arduino collection not received by Linnaeus until 1763 and not original material for the name. See notes by Jarvis (in 
<emphasis italics="true" pageNumber="732">Webbia</emphasis>
48: 497. 1994) on the large number of different taxa included within this name by Linnaeus.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
